1. Railway.app (Best for beginners, free tier, easy setup)
Pros: Free tier, always-on for small bots, super easy GitHub integration, no credit card required.
Cons: Free tier has monthly usage limits (but enough for most bots).
How:
Go to https://railway.app/ and sign up.
Click "New Project" â†’ "Deploy from GitHub repo" (connect your repo).
Set your BOT_TOKEN as an environment variable in the Railway dashboard.
Railway auto-detects Python and runs your bot.
Done! Your bot is live.